Class ManagerGenerate

java.lang.Object
org.knowledge.finder.generate.ManagerGenerate
public class ManagerGenerate extends Object
The ManagerGenerate class coordinates the generation of lessons and context files.

It acts as a high-level manager, initializing the required data structures and delegating the processing workflow to ContextGenerate. This class is typically used as the main entry point for generating project content from input files.

  • Constructor Details

    • ManagerGenerate

      public ManagerGenerate(String[] archivefiles, String archiveDir, String inputFile, String outputFile, String projectName, String lessonFolderName, String contextLinkPage)
      Constructs a ManagerGenerate instance with all required configuration parameters.

      This constructor initializes the lesson data and context generator, preparing the system for processing input files and generating output content.

      Parameters:
      archivefiles - array of file names to be archived after processing
      archiveDir - directory where archived files will be stored
      inputFile - input file containing raw lesson or webpage content
      outputFile - output file for processed context
      projectName - name of the project (used as root directory)
      lessonFolderName - prefix for lesson folder names
      contextLinkPage - hyperlink reference to the context file for generated lessons

  • Method Details

    • process

      public void process()
      Executes the full generation workflow for lessons and context files.

      This method delegates processing to the ContextGenerate instance, which handles reading input, generating output files, and organizing project structure.
